\code{unique(ard$context)} first and key to match (or pass a single
format string / \verb{default =} to cover everything). When an
explicitly-supplied \code{statistic} matches no context at all,
\code{pivot_across()} warns rather than silently emitting \code{{n}}.\tabular{ll}{
   Generating function \tab \code{context} to key on \cr
   \code{cards::ard_summary()} \tab \code{summary} \cr
   \code{cards::ard_tabulate()} \tab \code{tabulate} \cr
   \code{cards::ard_continuous()} \tab \code{continuous} \cr
   \code{cards::ard_categorical()} \tab \code{categorical} \cr
   \code{cards::ard_stack_hierarchical()} \tab \code{tabulate} + \code{hierarchical} \cr
   \code{cardx::ard_categorical_ci()} \tab \code{proportion_ci} \cr
   \code{cardx::ard_continuous_ci()} \tab \code{continuous_ci} \cr
}

